## Run Commands

> **Important:** Your system uses **Node 12** by default. Vite requires Node 18+, which is now installed via nvm.

**To run the frontend every time:**
```bash
/home/great/.nvm/versions/node/v18.20.8/bin/node \
  /home/great/.nvm/versions/node/v18.20.8/bin/npm run dev
```
Or add this alias to your fish config (`~/.config/fish/config.fish`):
```fish
alias node18 "/home/great/.nvm/versions/node/v18.20.8/bin/node"
alias npm18 "/home/great/.nvm/versions/node/v18.20.8/bin/npm"
```
Then just: `node18 node_modules/.bin/vite`

**To run the server:**
```bash
node server.js  # works with any Node version
```

